(1\) Selectors \(How CSS chooses elements\)) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Core selector types) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(- Element selector: targets all elements of that tag.) Tj
T*
(  - Example: p { color: white; }) Tj
T*
(- Class selector: reusable style for many elements.) Tj
T*
(  - Example: .header-button { border-radius: 6px; }) Tj
T*
(- ID selector: one unique element only.) Tj
T*
(  - Example: #title-name { font-weight: bold; }) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
([IMPORTANT] Prefer classes for reusable styles. Avoid duplicate IDs.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Selector combinations) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(- Descendant selector: .header-icons a means links inside .header-icons.) Tj
T*
(- Multiple selectors: .card, .panel { padding: 16px; }) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Example:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(```css) Tj
T*
(.card h2 {) Tj
T*
(    font-size: 24px;) Tj
T*
(}) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(.card,) Tj
T*
(.panel {) Tj
T*
(    border: 1px solid rgb\(68, 152, 114\);) Tj
T*
(}) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
